<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Halifax_Explosion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=23" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.cbc.ca/halifaxexplosion/" class="external text" title="http://www.cbc.ca/halifaxexplosion/" rel="nofollow">CBC Halifax Explosion Web Site</a> a large interactive web site about the explosion</li>
<li><a href="http://archives.cbc.ca/IDD-1-70-971/disasters_tragedies/halifax_explosion/" class="external text" title="http://archives.cbc.ca/IDD-1-70-971/disasters_tragedies/halifax_explosion/" rel="nofollow">The Halifax Explosion - CBC Archives</a> with video clips</li>
<li><a href="http://museum.gov.ns.ca/mma/AtoZ/HalExpl.html" class="external text" title="http://museum.gov.ns.ca/mma/AtoZ/HalExpl.html" rel="nofollow">The Maritime Museum of the Atlantic Halifax Explosion web page</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.gov.ns.ca/nsarm/virtual/remembrance/" class="external text" title="http://www.gov.ns.ca/nsarm/virtual/remembrance/" rel="nofollow">The Nova Scotia Archives Halifax Explosion Book of Remembrance</a>, a database of victims with 1,950 names</li>
<li><a href="http://www.gov.ns.ca/nsarm/virtual/explosion/" class="external text" title="http://www.gov.ns.ca/nsarm/virtual/explosion/" rel="nofollow">A Vision of Regeneration</a>, the explosion and reconstruction by the Nova Scotia Archives</li>
<li><a href="http://www.region.halifax.ns.ca/community/explode.html" class="external text" title="http://www.region.halifax.ns.ca/community/explode.html" rel="nofollow">Halifax Regional Municipality Halifax Explosion webpage and list of monuments</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.collectionscanada.ca/education/firstworldwar/05180202/0518020203_e.html" class="external text" title="http://www.collectionscanada.ca/education/firstworldwar/05180202/0518020203_e.html" rel="nofollow">Halifax Explosion Web Page - Library and Archives of Canada</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.halifaxexplosion.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.halifaxexplosion.org/" rel="nofollow">HalifaxExplosion.org</a> a web page created by Prince Andrew High School students and Saint Mary's University</li>
<li><a href="http://atlas.gc.ca/site/english/index.html" class="external text" title="http://atlas.gc.ca/site/english/index.html" rel="nofollow">Map of Halifax as it existed in 1915</a> - "The Atlas of Canada" archives</li>
<li><a href="http://ns1763.ca/hfxrm/unidentified1917.html" class="external text" title="http://ns1763.ca/hfxrm/unidentified1917.html" rel="nofollow">Photographs of the memorial to the Unidentified Dead, Halifax Explosion</a></li>
<li><a href="http://boston.about.com/od/historylandmarks/p/christmastree.htm" class="external text" title="http://boston.about.com/od/historylandmarks/p/christmastree.htm" rel="nofollow">The Boston Christmas Tree</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.halifaxfiremuseum.org/explosion.html" class="external text" title="http://www.halifaxfiremuseum.org/explosion.html" rel="nofollow">Halifax Firefighters Museum</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.nfb.ca/objectifdocumentaire/index.php?mode=view&amp;filmId=30&amp;language=english&amp;sort=title" class="external text" title="http://www.nfb.ca/objectifdocumentaire/index.php?mode=view&amp;filmId=30&amp;language=english&amp;sort=title" rel="nofollow">Watch the NFB documentary, <i>Just One Big Mess": The Halifax Explosion, 1917</i></a></li>
</ul>
